HONORED to have this new painting hanging at the MAC Gallery. Instead of chalky white gesso, I simply used rabbit skin glue to size the canvas. I let areas of the canvas peek through uncovered. I love how it’s natural color rhymes with the Naples yellow oil paint. I plan to explore this effect further. 
💥 OAKSCAPE, 47x59”(119x150cm), oil, emulsion, charcoal/ canvas.

SCROLL to see my latest painting on paper (three days ago). It’s similar to a larger one I painted on canvas. I’m enjoying the process of painting a few landscapes on paper that’s stapled to the wall in my studio. I wouldn’t necessarily say I get bored easily (maybe I do?) but I like to keep mixing things up, keeps me on my toes… Do you feel the same? There are no right answers I’m sure!

RAPHAEL COPY- 16”x12” (41x30cm), ink with bamboo carved pen on laid paper. I took on this difficult challenge (for me), faithfully freehand, mark for mark from an online hi resolution picture. Very little of the Raphaels impossibly ‘light hand’ rubbed off on me that’s for certain, but it never hurts to try, and it was three hours of fun practice and total distraction.  The drawing is of the suicide of Lucretia #lucretia which I found out was an enormously popular subject around the 16th century.  Do you know the story of Lucretia? I didn’t! 
.
#renaissancedrawing #raphaelartista #inkonpaperdrawing #drawingpractice #drawingtechnique #copydrawing #learnfrommasters #artpractice #drawingonpaper #drawingchallenges #renaissanceart #classicalart #draperydrawing
